<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 This document proposes the adoption of a new airworthiness directive (AD) that is applicable to certain Aerospatiale
Model ATR42 series airplanes. This proposal would require an inspection to determine the model and orientation of
certain flight control rods, and replacement with modified rods, if necessary. This proposal is prompted by reports
of corrosion found on the pitch trim and rudder trim rods. The actions specified by the proposed AD are intended to prevent
problems associated with corrosion of the flight control rods, which could compromise the required strength of these
items.



